<P>
   ARBITRATION-MARKETPLACE (New York) _ The New York Stock Exchange
may be the market of choice for investors who want the best
execution of their securities trades, but for those lodging
complaints against their brokers, the Exchange's arbitration
department appears to be the one in which they are less likely to
succeed, says Jonathan Kord Lagemann, a securities lawyer in New
York, who has studied the results of customer arbitration cases
filed at nine self-regulatory organizations since 1980.
