<HEADLINE>
AT A GLANCE: 1998 DODGE GRAND CARAVAN ES MINIVAN
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Package: Five-door, seven-passenger, V-6 powered,
extended-length, front-drive minivan.
</P>
<P>
   Highlights: Nice aerodynamic styling, roomy and comfortable,
lots of extras, zippy new 3.8- liter V-6, smooth four-speed
automatic transmission.
</P>
<P>
   Negatives: Higher maintenance and lower resale value than some
of the imports.
</P>
<P>
   Major competitors: Toyota Sienna, Chrysler Town &AMP; Country, Ford
Windstar, Mercury Villager/Nissan Quest; Honda Odyssey/Isuzu Oasis;
Chevy Venture/Pontiac Trans Sport/Olds Silhouette.
</P>
<P>
   EPA fuel economy: 17 miles per gallon city, 24 highway.
</P>
<P>
   Base price: $26,605 plus $580 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   Price as tested: $29,325, including transportation.
</P>
<P>
   On The Road rating: A.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
