boyhood pals Matt Damon and Ben Affleck, isn't the masterpiece the
Academy Award voters would have you believe. But what it is _ a
literate, beautifully acted, character-driven movie _ has become so
rare at the multiplex that it seemed revolutionary when it hit
screens last winter. (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
7/8.
