<P>
   &UR; General Features &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ALTERNATIVE-TRADE (Undated) _ ``Alternative trade
organizations'' _ mail-order groups devised to improve local
economies in developing nations, were popular in the 1980s and
early 1990s. But tougher competition has taken its toll, with only
four such groups with sales of more than $1 million remaining in
the U.S. today. By Sara Silver.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-PENSIONS (Undated) _ Nearly 1,400 Americans are
collecting pension benefits because they found their names on an
Internet site created by the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corp., the
federal agency that insures pensions. The agency posted the names
of about 8,600 people who have not applied for benefits due to them
from plans the agency now administers. By David Cay Johnston.
</P>
