   SPEND-CHILD-CARE (Undated) _ A growing number of companies pay
for child care when their employees must travel as part of their
jobs. But some question whether a benefit like this helps employees
have a more satisfying personal life, or simply keeps them on the
job and away from home longer. By Julia Lawlor.
</P>
<P>
   SPEND-NAVAJO-FOUNDATION (Gallup, N.M.) _ The Southwest Indian
Foundation enjoys a sterling reputation on the Navajo Reservation,
where it is a refuge of last resort for needy families. But it is
the group's direct-mail catalogue which the outside world sees, and
which raises questions about the mixing of charity and business.
Photo. By Jon Christenson.
</P>
