<P>
   CAR-SMART (Undated) _ A lot of convertibles shake, rattle and
roll. They leak and squeak, and, without the integral bracing of
solid tops, they flex like sponges when you wring them out on
bouncy roads. Outside the Sun Belt, they require 6 to 10 months of
compromise for 2 to 6 months of wind-blown freedom. This accepted
wisdom is fast becoming out of date. Photo. By James G. Cobb.
</P>
