A0125 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BRAVES-ONDECK11-COX     07-10 0296
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BRAVES-ONDECK11-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On deck: Florida Marlins
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 7:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Pro Player Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: TBS, WSB 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP Greg Maddux (12-2, 1.54; 7-1,
2.07 lifetime vs. Marlins) vs. RHP Ryan Dempster (1-3, 6.43; 0-0,
3.00 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Maddux is churning out pitching lines almost by rote. He
has pitched complete games in five of his last seven starts, has
three shut-outs in his last six games and has given up 41 hits
while striking out 53 in his last 58 innings. Maddux hasn't been
beaten since falling 7-6 to Colorado on April 26. He is 10-0 in his
subsequent 13 starts. He leads the NL in ERA (1.54), winning
percentage (.857), shutouts (4), is tied with Tom Glavine for most
wins (12) and is second in complete games (6). The league is
hitting .209 against him. He is on pace to set career marks in
victories (he has won 20 games twice) and complete games (he has
posted 10 twice) and has already tied his career-high for shutouts.
He beat the Marlins 6-2 on June 17 and could have had a shutout in
that game too, but a Tony Graffanino error in the fourth led to a
pair of earned runs. Watch his at-bats against Edgar Renteria. The
Marlins shortstop has a career .385 average (5-for-13) against
Maddux. Dempster, another Marlins rookie making his eighth major
league start, faced the Braves on June 18 but drew no decision in
Florida's 3-2 victory. He has allowed just two earned runs in his
last two outings, beating Boston on June 28 for his first victory
and then lasting just 3 1/3 innings against Montreal on July 4.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
